                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d49">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72/1782</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Italy</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_PTN1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Page</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Rome</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-05-20T12:00:00+01:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 20, 1915, 12 noon</hi>.</date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 1 p. m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>284. It is believed Chamber which meets to-day will sustain Government’s action,
                    probably appointing a committee to hear statement of its program including
                    credits to be asked, and that the committee will report favorably and its report
                    will be sustained to-morrow. Senate will then vote and war will almost certainly
                    follow.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_PTN1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Nelson Page</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
